H0.text: Four is the number of phases in which mitosis actually occurs.

H1.text: Seven is the number of phases in which mitosis actually occurs.

H2.text: Six is the number of phases in which mitosis actually occurs.

H3.text: Two is the number of phases in which mitosis actually occurs.

A4.text: The process of mitosis is divided into stages corresponding to the completion of one set of activities and the start of the next. These stages are preprophase (specific to plant cells), prophase, prometaphase, metaphase, anaphase, and telophase.
